          <source>C Assignment Operators</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>An assignment operation assigns the value of the right-hand operand to the storage location named by the left-hand operand.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Therefore, the left-hand operand of an assignment operation must be a modifiable l-value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>After the assignment, an assignment expression has the value of the left operand but is not an l-value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
